FBIS4-33079 "drlat106_a_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Soldiers Honored for Preventing `Hijacking' Soldiers Honored for Preventing `Hijacking' FL0106232294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1949 GMT 1 Jun 94 FL0106232294 Havana Radio Reloj Network Spanish BFN [Text] Revolutionary Armed Forces and Interior Ministry [Minint] distinguished service medals have been presented to a group of young soldiers who, on 27 May, prevented five individuals from hijacking a fishing boat and taking it to the Yankee base. The medals were presented to Minint noncommissioned officers Misael Valentin Furnier, who is recovering from the gunshots received during the operation, and Norberto Duran, as well as civilian Arnel Lopez, captain of the hijacked boat. Ensign David Antonio Casamayer and soldiers Idilio Vargas, Jose Alexander y Sada, Rafael Montero, Giosvani Barrios, and Andres Solano, all members of the Border Guard troops, were also presented medals. Juan Carlos Robinson, member of the Central Committee and first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Guantanamo, stressed the bravery of the young soldiers and their attitude toward those who tried to violate Cuban law.
